" crab mentality" - a metaphor apparently intrinsic to Filipino culture defind as the collective effort of the many with unreasonable thinking or instinct disseminate unfounded rumors or negative innuendos to bring down a target principal idea, society, institution or individuals. Similar to crabs void of instinct trying to cling to others pulling down the rest of the crabs in the chain back to the bottom of the bushel foiling success to escape.